    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The randomised study analyzes the effects of immediate bonding (skin-to-skin contact) on
      different psychobiological and somatic outcomes of mother and child. The investigators
      compare 3 bonding conditions. Cortisol and Oxytocin are also measured during the bonding
      process.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
